# iteration scratch: the /bin/cp backup taken before a big swing, and the ad-hoc
# probe/shot scripts an iteration writes to verify itself. Ignored so a killed
# iteration's leftovers can't make run-loop.sh refuse to start on a "dirty" tree.
#
# Anchored to the repo root ON PURPOSE. Unanchored (`probe-*.mjs`) these matched at
# every depth, so a probe that earned its keep could only be committed with `git add
# -f` — and the ledger spent ~20 iterations citing probes the repo did not contain
# (iter 101). Scratch is born at the root and ignored; a probe graduates by moving
# into `.claude/skills/grow-city/probes/`, which is tracked like any other source.
/before.html
/probe-*.mjs
/shot-*.mjs
